## Conversation
PR-B of the 2-PR stack: make the Stainless client the default and delete the
hand-rolled RemoteHTTPTraceServer. Builds on PR-A's parity work.

## Actions
- weave_init.py: init_weave_get_server always builds StainlessRemoteHTTPTraceServer;
  removed the should_use_stainless_server branch + import.
- settings.py: removed the use_stainless_server field (UserSettings + the env
  TypedDict) and should_use_stainless_server().
- api.py: removed the use_stainless_server doc entry.
- weave_client.py: made the parallel-table-upload capability probe
  implementation-agnostic — it now calls the typed table_create_from_digests
  instead of reaching for the hand-rolled-only _post_request_executor.__wrapped__;
  updated 2 stale comments.
- wal_sender.py: switched to StainlessRemoteHTTPTraceServer + set_auth() (the
  Stainless client has no auth= ctor kwarg).
- Deleted weave/trace_server_bindings/remote_http_trace_server.py.
- Test migration: trace_server_bindings/conftest (server_class always Stainless;
  removed the pytest_ignore_collect dual-impl logic); test_trace_server_bindings
  (removed the dead RemoteHTTPTraceServer branch + now-unused httpx import);
  test_weave_init_availability + test_wave_client_file_cache (→ Stainless);
  trace_server/conftest (flag now vestigial, default flipped to "stainless");
  tests/conftest network_proxy_client fixture rebuilt to inject a
  TestClient-backed SDK client + no-op _update_client_headers. Deleted
  test_http_behavior_remote.py + test_tags_aliases_routes.py.

## Errors & Mistakes
- test_table_partitioning[True] failed (0 table_create_from_digests calls): the
  capability probe asserted server._post_request_executor (a hand-rolled-only
  internal the Stainless client lacks) → AssertionError → probe reported the
  endpoint missing → parallel chunking silently skipped. Fixed by calling the
  typed method.

## Dead Ends
- ASGITransport (async) can't back the SDK's sync client; used FastAPI
  TestClient (a sync httpx.Client subclass) as the SDK's http_client.

## Hints for Future Agents
- The --remote-http-trace-server pytest flag is now vestigial (single impl);
  kept for CI compat with the default flipped to "stainless".
- network_proxy_client drives the SDK through a TestClient ASGI app and no-ops
  _update_client_headers so the injected client isn't .copy()'d away mid-request.

## Codebase Discoveries
- Client-side coupling to hand-rolled internals was localized to one spot
  (weave_client.py's _post_request_executor probe). No other coupling found.

